cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of estimating human poses from images. The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of benchmarks and empirical results suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of normalization techniques to improve the learning of convolutional spatial models suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
